Well, so, that's how I flew today.
First criticism point: We need more attractive logbooks. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it was finally... I flew a plane today. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from FlightAware.
I'm trying to go there again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look very good right now, but it's still Monday.
It's already clear where the problems lie. It is probably going to be VERY difficult to obtain the medical clearance, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will take VERY long time and means a LOT of extra work.
That's rather discouraging, but it's still just another problem that one has to solve. So far, it seems solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what awaits me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't let you get a medical exemption if you're taking medication for it.
